ped by Philipp\nKoehn and Josh Schroeder for processing the `Europarl corpus <http://www.statmt.org/europarl/>`_.\n\nThe module is a port of `Lingua::Sentence Perl module <http://search.cpan.org/perldoc?Lingua::Sentence>`_ with\nsome extra additions (improved non-breaking prefix lists for some languages and added support for Danish,\nFinnish, Lithuanian, Norwegian (Bokm\u00e5l), Romanian, and Turkish).\n\n\n"], "modules": [{"name": "sentence_splitter", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "sentence_splitter.split_text_into_sentences", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "text", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "language", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "non_breaking_prefix_file", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}], "returns": {"name": "List", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.List", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "documentation": ["Split text into sentences.\n\nFor better performance, use SentenceSplitter class directly to avoid reloading non-breaking prefix file on every\ncall.\n\n```\nparam text\n\nText to be split into individual sentences\n\nparam language\n\nISO 639-1 language code\n\nparam non_breaking_prefix_file\n\npath to non-breaking prefix file\n\nreturn\n\nList of string sentences\n```\n"]}], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "sentence_splitter.SentenceSplitterException", "bases": ["Exception"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Sentence splitter exception."]}, {"name": "sentence_splitter.SentenceSplitterWarning", "bases": ["Warning"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_class